{
  "query": "What is the most effective design for an artificial nest box intended for bumblebees?",
  "relevant_summary": "The most effective artificial nest box design for bumblebees is an underground box entirely buried 5-10 cm below ground level with a 30-80 cm long entrance pipe, which achieved occupancy rates between 6% and 58% in trials (Action 48). This design significantly outperforms wooden surface or above-ground nest boxes, which showed very low occupancy rates of 0-1.5% in recent UK trials (Action 48). Underground boxes made from various materials including tin, wood, or terracotta were tested across the USA, Canada, and UK, with all studies demonstrating superior performance compared to above-ground alternatives (Action 48).",
